Open Post to Chet, DocDel, John, Professor, others:<br><br>
1. Many posts back I told a brief tale about my being an American volunteer who was in Israel during the summer of 1967 (The famous 6 day war).  I was there because I am a Jew. I felt my fight was with my Brothers and Sisters, there, and not against another race of people (Vietnamese), or political system (North Viet Nam), and I went to fight for what I believed, choosing to not run to Canada and hide.<br><br>
2. Doc Del, I am utterly horrified and outraged by what your last post said. The cementary vandalized by a mainland hate group got no media coverage over here. NONE.  From what we have shared, both publicly and privately, I would stand by you, shoulder to shoulder, anytime and anyplace. I would also continue to learn from you, if you permit, as you do have a better &quot;grip&quot; on racial diversity and understanding than I do. And I freely admit that.  Please send me info on what happened, and how, in any form, matter, or my long standing relationship with many law enforcement folks here, how I can help, if I can.<br><br>
3. Chet, the same thinking and feeling that I just told Doc, apply to you. Apparently &quot;we&quot; have un-earthed the worms, the slugs of humanity by picking up the rock called racial attitudes.  If for one moment I thought that my sharing my own mental stumbling would be seen as an encouragement for that slime, I would never have posted. I stumbled, and I learn, that seems to be my style. I realize that I have to clearly be more careful, given how many trollers we seem to have. Another bitter lesson.  <br><br>
4. John, see my post of 4/24. I readily took my &quot;hit&quot; and re-thought old and stale thinking. Yes, there was, I repeat, was, a possible racist undertone. I think it came from years of lazy non-thinking, as I wrote, and a small and biased sample pool of subjects, plus a paranoid creep of a neighbor. The race of my neighbor should never have factored into my anger at him, and I now realize that wrong. <br><br>
I do not know many Vietnamese, socially or personally. Two of my working-friends-associates are both Chinese (Jesus, that sounds like I am saying &quot;some of my best friends are Jews.....and we ALL know what anti-sematic bullshit that is).... The fact is that out of my own ignorance came the wrong conclusions, and I re-thought, and grew past it.  <br><br>
Doc, I am so utterly blown away by what was done to your daughters grave.  F*** those idiots who have to spew hate via e-mail. What you discribed is far more serious. Just like the &quot;almost biological bomb&quot; that the Banai Brith got in Washington D.C. yesterday. What can i do to help you? <br><br>
Hatred comes in all colors, and in all disguises.  Yes, I have hatred too, hatred for those who hate me, hatred for those who slaughtered all my relatives in WW2, and hatred for anyone who wants to F*** with any friend of mine.<br><br>
This thread has become a snake. What do we do with it. Smash the rock back down on it, or expose it to the light of day?<br><br>
doc spatz
